<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9305: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-12T20:00:00-04:00">August 12, 1937—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>144. Reference Shanghai’s 458, August 12, 7 p.m., second paragraph,
                                and Department’s 141, August 12, 2 p.m.<note n="85" xml:id="d426fn85">Latter not printed.</note> The Department
                                authorizes you, in your discretion, to make the representations
                                recommended by Shanghai.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>